# Project Overview

**UNHCR Bulgarian Language Platform** — free interactive app for refugees learning Bulgarian. Currently scoped to A1 (11 lessons + 6 tests, ~9 lessons digitalised); the codebase is structured to host A2, B1, B2 in the same repo.

**Stack:** Next.js 15 App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui, Drizzle ORM + Neon PostgreSQL, JWT auth (HTTP-only cookies), dnd-kit.

**7 languages:** `bg` (default), `ar`, `en`, `fr`, `fa`, `uk`, `ru` — RTL: `ar`, `fa`.

**i18n:** `useT()` → static UI strings pre-translated in [src/i18n/ui.ts](mdc:src/i18n/ui.ts). `useTranslate()` → dynamic content via Google Translate API + localStorage cache. Exercise words/answers always stay in Bulgarian — never translate them.

## Content Layout (Multi-Level)

- `src/content/shared/` — types, EXERCISE_TEMPLATES, TEST_TEMPLATES (shared by ALL levels — change once, applies everywhere)
- `src/content/a1/`, `src/content/a2/`, `src/content/b1/`, `src/content/b2/` — per-level lessons & tests, each with its own `index.ts` registry
- `src/content/registry.ts` — aggregates all levels into a single loader + lookup map (`loadLesson(id)`, `loadTest(id)`, `LESSON_LEVEL_MAP`, etc.)
- `src/content/index.ts` — public barrel; legacy helpers (`navItems`, `getLessonMetadata`, `getTestFolder`, …) still work for backward-compat

A1 lesson IDs stay un-prefixed (`lesson-XX`) so existing user progress keeps working. A2+ lesson IDs are level-prefixed (`a2-lesson-XX`, …). Test IDs already include the level (`test-a1-1`, `test-a2-1`, …).

**Onboarding a new collaborator:** see [ONBOARDING.md](mdc:ONBOARDING.md).

**Status:** A1 lessons 0–8 + tests 1–3 fully digitalised. Lessons 9–11 + tests 4–6 are placeholders. A2/B1/B2 are skeleton folders ready for content.

For content/lesson work → see `content-lessons` rule. For UI/component work → see `design-system` rule.
